  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TIM1.10">
<l>talaiyāya vaintiṉaiyuñ cātittut tāḻntu</l>
<l>talaiyā yiṉavuṇarntōrkāṇpar talaiyāya</l>
<l>vaṇṭattā ṉātiraiyā ṉālāla muṇṭiruṇṭa</l>
<l>kaṇṭattāṉ cempoṟ kaḻal</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who adhere to the five [practices?] that are foremost,</l>
<l>lower [themselves] [and] perceive what is foremost, they will see</l>
<l>the red-golden anklets of him whose throat is darkened by eating the Hālāla,</l>
<l>him of Ārdrā, the one of the universe who is the head.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
